opic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   60 Epic Mage vs 60 Epic Shaman - need tactics</span><hr size=1> Ok I have a 60 Shaman friend of mine who keeps giving me crap about wanting to duel me.  I figure I may have a chance to beat his *once* if I have a trick or two up my sleeve.<br>
<br>
He has Torpor, that's why I don't think I can win.<br>
<br>
I have my Epic, and a couple of instaclick nuke wands (from Undertow and Plane of Hate).<br>
<br>
We haven't come up with a place or any conditions yet.<br>
<br>
So, any way I can tilt this in my favor to get the jump on him?<br>
<br>
PS-My sig says 59, but I should ding 60 soon and that's when he wants to duel.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=320028" target="_blank">Xenditil</a><BR>
Epic Gnome Mage of the 59th Rod of Transcendence<BR>
Master Tinkerer (180)<BR>
The Kindred<BR>
Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureinny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>reinny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(9/15/02 12:03:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 60 Epic Mage vs 60 Epic Shaman - need tactics</span><hr size=1> banishment his pet first ,, mostlikely he well  try to malo your epic pet and root/slow it and dot u. shammy dots have long cast time.. no match for you scar of sig so just bolt kite him, if u are fighting in arena with small space u are out of luck on bolt kite. if u are fighting in large area like whole zone banish his pet mala him, at this time if your pet is rooted/blinded run away on your horse summon companion dispell malo/root on pet go at him again with fresh pet. nuke him while his trying to malo/root your pet again... most shammy well not fight on horse btw.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urenlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Renlan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 5:33:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   How about 54 ghetto Mage vs 49 Shaman?</span><hr size=1> The resident shaman in our small guild just hit 49 and his new spells have made him somewhat brash, hence his challenge to me. Believe it or not, I've never really dueled anyone and it'll be horrible if I'm toppled by someone 5 levels my junior!<br>
<br>
Anyone have any advice on tactics and also rules we might use? He has suggested both of us buff/summon to our hearts content and mana back to full, although I think this really gives him the advantage. Any other thoughts?<br>
<br>
-Renlan, 54 Ghetto Mage of Slege Gan Licgan<br>
Mithaniel Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reinny>reinny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/02 2:34:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   my exp against 60/60 shammy </span><hr size=1> dont know if u are dueling in inclosed space or in open space, but I tell u one of my encounters with shammy in SZ. 60 evil epic shammy and I(lv60 magi on good team) allmost found each other same time in DC. We were both in levi state he had pet and i had pet, I sent in my pet and started casting mala on him. about time my mala landed on him he landed malo on me at this time his pet and my pet were fighting. As i was trying to cast char I saw him casting another spell, shammy dots are very nasty and cant not be disspelled so i could not afford to get hit by even one of his dots so i moved back out of his casting range. around this time my epic pet had killed his pet and was on him, so he made smart choice and went under water out of my sight, so he can deal with pet alone otherwise I would nuke him down. as i was looking for him he maloed the epic pet root/slowed him however root was  breaking very often and I could tell he was having very hard time with pet. still i recalled my pet, anulled few times to dispell slow,malo on pet, and rebuffed pet. when i assisted my pet to check shammy hp he was 1/3 hp, but i assumed his back to full hp somewhere and meding. I ran around for 2-3 minet looking for shammy and some how i found him meding between rockcleffs. the shammy began to run this time toward the zone line attempting to zone plug. All I could do at this situation was just run along with my pet on his ass because magi spells are dame too slow its near impossible to  land a nuke on a fast moving target while on horse, him being fat evil ogre shammy with tones of hp ran allway up to zone line and died inchs from the zone line. If I had not found the shammy by luck that soon in dc i would have proly have lost that fight, du to shammys dot that cant not be annuled by magi + torper. So duel inside inclosed space such as arena u have better chance of winning, if open space shammy have better chance of winning cuz they can just dot u run away come back later and finish u off,but could go ether way depending on who finds who offguard first.(if u are outdoor and u dont have velocity then u loss cuz u cant chase sowed shammy with out velocity, also only epic pet+ veloicty can chase down horse). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reinny>reinny</A> at: 11/24/02 2:39:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nucci01>Nucci 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(11/29/02 4:21:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my exp against 60/60 shammy </span><hr size=1> Don't forget that shaman DOTs can be cured with counteract poison/disease potions that those very same shaman make  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Duels often come down to who is the most prepared and willing to take it the fartherest.<br>
