</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=belarkan>Belarkan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 1:07:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my exp against 60/60 shammy </span><hr size=1> Once you get around 200 RD and 200 RP, the only thing a shaman can do is run away and chain cast Torpor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Well maybe not, he can also cast his Epic DoT (RM based) which is semi lure but with a long cast time.<br>
<br>
-Belarkan. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nevilleaoryn>Neville Aoryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 4:11:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my exp against 60/60 shammy </span><hr size=1> Im not a mage or shammy but i've fought both so i may be able to help.  One thing is as reinny said he will try to root your pet or blind it, so dispel the pet as soon as that happens.  Shammies dots can easily be dispelled with a few dots, im only 51 but i was able to keep myself dot free with a stack of counteract disease/poison pots.  Get a nice cold res cause once he gets tired of having his dots dispelled over and over, he'll start nuking you, with 180ish CR you'll resist np at which point he'll be dead from your pet, GL<br>
Neville Illusionist of Frostborn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garndtz>Garndtz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 1:32:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   PvP</span><hr size=1> Also, before your pet buffs himself, buff him with see invis. Then go about buffing pet normally. After pet is completely buffed, use cancel magic on him and it will take off see invis. Now his top spot is open so you can just cancel magic if pet gets rooted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soulstisfallenhope>soulstis fallenhope</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 8:31:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 60 Epic Mage vs 60 Epic Shaman - need tactics</span><hr size=1> Don't forget our wonderful little summoned staffs with one charge of cancel. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=319137">Soutstis Fallenhope </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
